HK stocks seen range - bound in quiet trade . Hong Kong stocks are expected to consolidate within a tight range on Friday on a lack of fresh incentives , brokers said . " The market is likely to continue its consolidation in quiet trading ahead of the weekend , and the index will move within a 50 - point range today , " said Andrew To , dealing director at OSK Asia Securities . Beijing ' s measures to curb speculation on Chinese stock markets would also affect sentiment , he added . The Hang Seng Index eased 23 . 52 points to 14 , 212 . 00 on Thursday . Later , the Hang Seng London Reference Index added 11 . 93 points to 14 , 223 . 93 . - - Hong Kong newsroom ( 852 ) 2843 6369 
